public class NichePSO
extends Algorithm
implements OptimisationAlgorithm

Title: NichePSO

Description: CILib (Computational Intelligence Library). This class defines the NichePSO which can be used to find multilple solutions within a search space.

The interested reader is referred to: Brits, R., (2002). Niching Strategies for Particle Swarm Optimization, University of Pretoria.

Author:
Clive Naicker

Constructor Detail

NichePSO

public NichePSO()
The default constructor. Initialises the mainSwarm to use the ZeroVelocityComponent, StandardAcceleration and StandardInertia. The acceleration is set to 1.2 and the inertia is set to 0.7. The maximum velocity is clamped to 0.5

getSwarmRadius

public double getSwarmRadius(PSO pso)
This method is used to determine the swarm radius of the PSO. The swarm radius is the largest distance from the best particle in the PSO to all other particles in the PSO.

Parameters:
pso - The PSO to determine the radius off.
Returns:
The radius of the PSO.

findClosestNeighbor

public static Particle findClosestNeighbor(Particle particle,
                                           Topology topology)
This is a utility method that will find the particle that is closest to the particle specified. The Euclidean distance is used to determine the closest particle. That is, the particle that has the smallest Euclidean distance to the specified particle is the closest particle.

Parameters:
particle - The specified particle to find the closest neighbor to it.
topology - The topology which contains the particles neighbors.
Returns:
The closest neighbor to the specified particle. If no particle could be found then null is returned.
